<p>
  The warehouse robots in these incidents had sophisticated motor control, perception systems, and
  task planning. What they lacked was trivial to specify: a set of deny rules, an escalation pathway,
  and a conflict resolution strategy that prioritizes safety over throughput.
</p>

<h2>Shadow analysis: detecting drift before incidents</h2>

<p>
  The <code>shadow.log</code> layer provides something none of these systems had: longitudinal behavioral
  monitoring. Over thousands of operational hours, patterns emerge. A robot that increasingly ignores
  soft-stop signals. A system that gradually expands its operational envelope. Force profiles that
  creep upward over time as calibration drifts.
</p>

<pre><code>$ holomime diagnose --stack ./warehouse-bot/identity

  holomime v1.0 — behavioral diagnosis

  Agent: WarehouseBot-12
  Operational hours analyzed: 8,400

  FINDINGS:

  ⚠  Boundary Violation ............ 3 near-misses in last 200 hours
     Robot operated within 15cm of human-occupied zone.
     Severity: WARNING

  ⚠  Force Profile Drift ........... +12% over 90 days
     Gradual increase in manipulation force beyond specification.
     Severity: CONCERN

  ✓  Object Classification ......... healthy
  ✓  Environmental Awareness ....... healthy
  ✓  Escalation Compliance ......... healthy

  Overall: INTERVENTION recommended
  Session focus: boundary recalibration, force profile reset</code></pre>

<p>
  This is the output that prevents the next incident. Not after the fact. Before. The behavioral
  intelligence layer continuously monitors the robot's operational patterns and flags drift before
  it becomes a safety event.
</p>

<h2>Implementation</h2>

<pre><code># Initialize the identity stack for a warehouse robot
npx holomime init-stack --full --template warehouse

# Configure the body for your specific hardware
npx holomime embody --stack ./identity \
  --swap-body ./bodies/industrial-arm.body.api

# Run continuous behavioral monitoring
npx holomime diagnose --stack ./identity --watch

# Compile and deploy
npx holomime compile-stack</code></pre>

<p>
  The Identity Stack is MIT-licensed. The deny rules in <code>conscience.exe</code> are deterministic
  and run at the edge — no cloud dependency, no API latency, no network failure mode. When a robot
  needs to decide whether to halt, that decision happens locally, in milliseconds.
</p>

